OL,6,FPaterson is currently due for release
OL,7,Fin 2027, but the Coroner's verdict
OL,8,Fcould lead to more charges against
OL,9,Fhim, although, given the delays, that
OL,10,Fis seemingly a long way off.
OL,12,FAndrew Chalklen is one of those
OL,13,Fanxiously waiting to find out if his
OL,14,Fwife Melanie's death was premature
OL,15,Fbecause of her surgery.
OL,17,FThe evidence has been heard in her
OL,18,Fcase, but he won't hear the conclusion
OL,19,Funtil all of the cases have been heard.
